]div
[div class=p 
	"This page serves as a collection of useful information for the English and Japanese versions of Paper Mario: The Thousand-Year Door.
	$LF
]div
[h2 id=GeneralKnowledge 
	" General Knowledge
	$LF
]h2
[h3 id=JapaneseRAMAddresses 
	"Japanese RAM Addresses
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"https://www.dropbox.com/s/9bjiojg4c11cscf/TTYDJP.CT?dl=0
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=RNG 
	"RNG
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"The Random Number Generator affects many things in this game, such as some spawn points and the movement of NPCs and enemies in the overworld and the effect an item has on an opponent in battle.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Some situations where RNG is advanced:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Every place where the game needs a random decision, such as:
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" jumping (the sound Mario makes)
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" the movement of the audience (nothing, jumping, turning around, etc.)
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" the movement of the NPCs (angle, duration of that angle, etc.)
				$LF
			]li
			[li 
				" the attack of the enemy
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
		" Displaying a letter (for each letter it's advanced twice, probably to avoid real time manipulation of the RNG)
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h2 id=TricksandGlitches 
	"Tricks and Glitches
	$LF
]h2
[h3 id=ActivateMayorOutside 
	"Activate Mayor Outside
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"After talking to the gatekeeper in Twilight Trail, Mario must go talk to the mayor. Normally, Mario would enter the mayor’s house and walk up to him to trigger a cutscene. By walking up against the right side of his house in paper mode, Mario can trigger the cutscene. This works because the mayor moves close enough to the edge of the house such that the cutscene trigger reaches slightly outside of the house.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"https://youtu.be/NLYKTwMfTVY
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=AvoidBillBlasterBattles 
	"Avoid Bill Blaster Battles
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"By positioning Mario between two Bill Blasters and flipping into Paper mode, you can walk right between the Blasters and avoid the battle entirely.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" This has applications in both the Pirate's Grotto in Chapter 5 (see the second clip of the second video in the table above) and the Palace of Shadow in Chapter 8.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"https://youtu.be/Ib48OEqyygg
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=BackgroundSkip 
	"Background Skip
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Near the end of the Chapter 7 factory room, after grabbing the card key, it is intended that you enter the pipe on the floor, go all the way to the left of the background, ride the platform up to the first pipe in the room, and then go up the stairs to Magnus. Instead, you can Spring Jump on the ground and, upon descent, land on the left or right moving platform, skipping traveling through the background again.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"https://youtu.be/2A4tUGVwtzA
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"In addition, you can hover with Yoshi from the card key platform to the top of the save block. This way, you can visually see when the platforms are moving and time when to Spring Jump onto them.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=BackwardsGoomther 
	"Backwards Goomther
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Sometimes during Goombella’s ability cutscene in the Prologue, Goomther, whom Goombella tattles to demonstrate her ability, can sometimes exit the screen walking backwards. We believe this is because the Goomther that is loaded in Rogueport Square (as opposed to the one loaded in the cutscene) turns around just as the Goomther in Goombella’s cutscene begins walking away.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=BillBlasterSkip 
	"Bill Blaster Skip
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"In Pirate’s Grotto in the bright room, Mario can either jump or hover with Yoshi around the Bill Blasters. This is because the platform past the blasters extends slightly farther up on the Z-axis compared to the bridge to the left.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"In the room before the boat, you can go into paper mode and walk behind the first set of bills and in front of the second set of bills in order to avoid encountering them. On the way back from the boat, you can skip the first bills by entering the room in paper mode and then moving left slightly before moving down. After this, you can use tube mode to jump over the second set of bills.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"https://youtu.be/E3pnqi1P2og
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=BlockSwitcheswithoutKoops 
	"Block Switches without Koops
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"When Mario jumps onto a switch that raises or lowers a block, there is 1 frame where the game can be paused. Once the game is unpaused, there is another 1 frame opportunity to jump off of the switch while activating it at the same time. This allows hitting some switches without Koops that would normally require his ability, which is particularly helpful when he is not already out.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" The most significant use of this trick is speed swapping off of the first blue switch outside Hooktail Castle and using the hammer on the second, allowing you to enter Hooktail Castle without using Koops.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
